    </section>
    <section id="id1172268459255">
      <title>Mellitic acid anhydride</title>

      <para id="id1172267795970">The anhydride of mellitic acid (<link target-id="id8182039"/>a) may be considered as an oxide of carbon since its chemical formula contains only carbon and oxygen, i.e., C<sub>12</sub>O<sub>9</sub> (<link target-id="id8182039"/>b). </para>

